rshot (1.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package.
  * Source modules relocated from share/shutter/resources/modules/ to
    share/shutter/perl/ per Debian Perl Policy §2.3; installed to
    /usr/share/perl5/Shutter/ via dh_install.
  * Drop the 'use lib' shim from bin/rshot; modules now resolve via @INC
    in both source-tree (share/shutter/perl) and installed
    (/usr/share/perl5/Shutter) layouts.
  * Drop XFIXES cursor-image support; rshot now uses the standard
    GDK_LEFT_PTR fallback in all cases.  Avoids the need to vendor
    X11-Protocol-Other::XFIXES, which Debian's libx11-protocol-perl does
    not ship.
  * Add debian/ for dpkg-buildpackage (control, rules, copyright,
    changelog, watch, source/format).  Follows Debian Policy 4.7.4.1.
  * Build is bit-for-bit reproducible (SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH +
    strip-nondeterminism).

 -- Ashley Brooks <runit@runit.lol>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 05:12:24 -0700
